title.rendered: United Arab Emirates vs Papua New Guinea, World Cup Qualifiers 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
United Arab Emirates vs Papua New Fantasy Team

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for UAE & PNG

UAE: Aryan Lakra, Muhammad Waseem (c), Vriitya Aravind, Rameez Shahzad, Aayan Afzal Khan, Asif Khan, Rohan Mustafa, Aryansh Sharma (wk), Junaid Siddique, Karthik Meiyappan, Zahoor Khan

PNG: Kiplin Doriga (wk), Hiri Hiri/Tony Ura, Sese Bau, Assad Vala (c), Charles Amini, Gaudi Toka, Norman Vanua, Riley Hekure, Chad Soper, Kabua Morea, John Kariko/Semo Kamea

Wanderers Cricket Ground, Windhoek Pitch Report

Venue: Wanderers Cricket Ground, Windhoek

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 238

2nd innings average score: 240

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Balanced

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 3rd T20I 2023: Fantasy Tips

Gujarat vs Chennai, Indian T20 League 2023: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Rohan Mustafa has done it all against PNG. Besides being the highest run-getter (382 at 48), he is the leading wicket-taker (13).

Assad Vala relishes playing at the Wanderers Cricket Ground. In four ODIs, he has added 226 runs at 57 and taken four wickets.

Sese Bau (248 at 35) and Tony Ura (206 at 35) are the second- and third-highest run-scorers for PNG against the UAE. Between them, they have slammed five fifties and four thirties in their last 10 ODIs.

For PNG, Chad Soper (15) and Riley Hekure (13) are the leading wicket-takers against the UAE. While Soper has the best figures of five for 25, Hekure’s best effort reads five for 13. 

Aayan Afzal Khan (59 runs and seven wickets) has featured in the Best11 for four consecutive ODIs.

In six ODIs versus PNG, Muhammad Waseem has accumulated 231 runs at 39 and has hammered the most sixes (16) by a UAE batter.

For the year, Zahoor Khan has bagged 13 wickets in 10 ODIs – of which five have come against PNG in four outings.

After four ODIs, Aryan Lakra averages only 15 against the UAE.
